ions that Wittgenstein raised in his works. The answers to the questions raised in this introduction may be found on the intersection between forms of life and radical translation from another culture into ours. The book presents an extensive analysis of anthropological issues with emphasis on language and social elements.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aPhilosophie. 4aPhilosophische Anthropologie. 4aWittgenstein. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh1 aBassols, Alejandro Tomasini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFogelin, Robert J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía-Carpintero, Manuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGálvez, Jesús Padilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHacker, P. M. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHertzberg, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanzian, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLagerspetz, Olli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarques, António, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPadilla Gálvez, Jesús, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUrsúa, Nicanor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVenturinha, Nuno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 20